{"title_page": "Oru Adaar Love", "text_new": "{{short description|2018 film by Omar Lulu}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Oru Adaar Love\n| image          = Oru Adaar Love (2018) Poster.jpg\n| alt            = The poster features Priya Prakash Varrier and Roshan Abdul Rahoof\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Omar Lulu]]\n| producer       = Ousepachan Vaalakuzhy\n| screenplay     = {{plainlist|\n* Sarang Jayaprakash\n* Lijo Panadan\n}}\n| story          = Omar Lulu\n| starring       = {{plainlist|\n*[[mohammad roshan]]\n*[[Noorin Shereef]]\n*[[Priya Prakash Varrier]]\n}}\n| narrator       = \n| music          = [[Shaan Rahman]]<br/> [[Gopi Sunder]]\n| cinematography = Sinu Sidharth\n| editing        = Achu Vijayan\n| studio         = Ousepachan Movie House\n| distributor    = Ousepachan Screen Media\n| released       = {{Film date|df=y|2019|2|14}}\n| runtime        = 145 minutes <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt7387300/|title=Oru Adaar Love|via=www.imdb.com}}</ref>\n| country        = India\n| language       = [[Malayalam]]\n| budget         = {{INR}}5 crore<ref name=\"gross\" />\n| gross          = {{INR}}12 crore<ref name=\"gross\" />\n}}\n'''''Oru Adaar Love''''' ({{translation |A fantastic love}}) is a 2019 Indian [[Malayalam]]-language [[romantic comedy]] film directed by [[Omar Lulu]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Soman|first1=Deepa|title=Omar Lulu's next film is 'Oru Adaar Love'|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/omar-lulus-next-film-is-oru-adaar-love/articleshow/60531587.cms|accessdate=12 February 2018|work=The Times of India|date= January 2018}}</ref> The screenplay was written by Sarang Jayaprakash and Lijo Panadan from a story by Omar Lulu, and produced by Ousepachan Vaalakuzhy under his production company Ousepachan Movie House.<ref name=\"manorama\"/> The film features [[Roshan Abdul Rahoof]], [[Noorin Shereef]], [[Priya Prakash Varrier]], [[Siyadh Shajahan]], [[Vaishak Pavanan]] and [[Michelle Ann Daniel]] and principal roles.\n\nThe story deals with [[Education in India|high school]] romance. [[Oru Adaar Love]] gained nationwide attention due to a clip which went viral, from the song \"Manikya Malaraya Poovi\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IkTlfPa_E8A|title=Priya Varrier: The actress whose wink stopped India|first=|last=|date=12 March 2018|publisher=BBC News|via=YouTube}}</ref> It prompted the makers to make changes in script, which delayed production.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telugu360.com/oru-adaar-love-reshoot-increase-length-character/|title=\"Oru Adaar Love\" reshoot to increase length of Character|date=9 April 2018|publisher=}}</ref> The film was released on 14 February 2019. It was dubbed and released in [[Tamil language|Tamil]] with the same title as [[Malayalam]] title, in [[Kannada]] as ''[[Kirik Love Story]]''<ref>{{citation|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/priya-prakash-varriers-kannada-dubbed-version-of-oru-adaar-love-to-release-on-valentines-day/articleshow/67349022.cms|title=Priya Prakash Varrier's Kannada dubbed version of 'Oru Adaar love' to release on valentine's day|date=2019-02-01|work=[[The Times of India]]}}</ref> and in [[Telugu language|Telugu]] as ''Lover's Day''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/allu-arjun-be-special-guest-lover-s-day-audio-launch-95459|work=The Newsminute |title=Allu Arjun to be special guest at 'Lover's Day' audio launch|date=22 January 2019|access-date=2019-01-23}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n\nThe story revolves around the journey of high school kids from the time they first meet during their first day of class in 11th class until their graduation day in 12th class. Roshan woos Priya with the help of Gadha and his other friends. One evening Roshan  his friends get drunk and a friend of Roshan accidentally sends a [[porn video]] from Roshan's phone to the school's WhatsApp group. This causes a wedge between Roshan and Priya. Roshan and Gadha then pretend to be in love to make Priya jealous but they end up having feelings for each other. Priya approaches Roshan and says that she is o forgive him and that they can start to be in a relationship again. But Roshan is unable to forget Gadha, which comes to be known by Priya. Heartbroken, she tells Roshan that Gadha alone is the perfect for him and they end their relationship. On graduation day, Roshan decides to propose to Gadha on top of the mountain. Just as Roshan is about to propose to Gadha, they are attacked by a bunch of goons who were antagonized by Roshan and Gadha earlier as part of an [[Eve teasing]] incident. When Gadha was about to be raped and Roshan to be killed, their friends enter and save them. The movie ends with them riding away happily.\n\n==Cast==\n{{colbegin}}\nPrincipal members of the cast are:<ref>{{cite news|last=Shrijith|first=Sajin|title=Trolling worked to our advantage, says 'Oru Adaar Love' producer Ousepachan Vaalakuzhy|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/2018/dec/17/everything-has-turned-out-well-1912401.html|accessdate=14 February 2019|work=[[The New Indian Express]]|date=17 December 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Roshan Abdul Rahoof]] as Roshan\n* [[Noorin Shereef]] as Gadha John\n* [[Priya Prakash Varrier]] as Priya Varrier\n* [[Siyadh Shajahan]] as Francis E. Manavalan\n* [[Mathew Joseph]] as Mathew\n* [[Arun A Kumar]] as Arun\n* [[Vaishak Pavanan]] as Vishakh aka 'Pavanna'\n* [[Michelle Ann Daniel]] as Michelle\n* [[Aneesh G Menon]] as Shibu Sir, Maths Teacher\n* [[Hareesh Kanaran]] as Unmesh Sir, P. T. Teacher\n* [[Roshna Ann Roy]] as Sneha Miss, Biology Teacher\n* [[Althaf Salim]] as Manikandan Sir, Chemistry Teacher\n* [[Anjali Nair]] as English Miss\n* [[Pradeep Kottayam]] as Principal's Secretary\n* [[Shivaji Guruvayoor]] as Principal\n* [[Siddique (actor)|Siddique]] as Jose Panadan, Sub-Inspector of Police\n* [[Sreejith Ravi]] as Divakaran, Constable of Police\n* [[Salim Kumar]] as Manavalan\n* [[Vishnu Govindan]] as the school peon\n* [[Dilruba Aswad Alqamar]] as Sana\n* [[Suhaid(Kukku)]] as Akku\n* [[Kalabhavan Niyas]] as Gadha's father\n{{colend}}\n\n==Production==\nFilming started on Januay 15, 2018.[http://onlookersmedia.in/latestnews/oru-adaar-love-omar-lulus-next-chunkzz-starts-rolling/ Oru Adaar Love: Omar Lulu\u2019s next after Chunkzz starts rolling!]\nMalayalam film producer Ousepachan Vaalakuzhy, impressed with Omar Lulu's ''[[Happy Wedding]]'' and ''[[Chunkzz]]'' decided to finance his third project, ''Oru Adaar Love''. The primary cast was selected through audition. Ousepachan Vaalakuzhy said he likes to promote newcomers, as has he done with his previous films.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u0d12\u0d2e\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d \u0d1a\u0d3f\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d46 \u0d1e\u0d3e\u0d28\u0d4d\u200d \u0d15\u0d3e\u0d23\u0d41\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d24\u0d4d \u0d12\u0d30\u0d41 \u0d2a\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d38\u0d4d\u0d31\u0d4d\u0d31\u0d40\u0d1c\u0d4d\u0d2f\u0d38\u0d4d \u0d38\u0d3f\u0d28\u0d3f\u0d2e\u0d2f\u0d3e\u0d2f\u0d3f- \u0d28\u0d3f\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d\u0d2e\u0d4d\u0d2e\u0d3e\u0d24\u0d3e\u0d35\u0d4d \u0d14\u0d38\u0d47\u0d2a\u0d4d\u0d2a\u0d1a\u0d4d\u0d1a\u0d28\u0d4d\u200d \u0d05\u0d2d\u0d3f\u0d2e\u0d41\u0d16\u0d02|url=https://southlive.in/movie/interview-movie/ousepachan-interview/|accessdate=12 February 2018|publisher=South Live|date=14 January 2018}}</ref> After Priya Prakash Varrier's wink in the song \"Manikya Malaraya Poovi\" became a viral hit, the makers altered the script to give prominence to her, thus sidelining the role played by Noorin Shereef, who had initially been cast in the lead role.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/videos/entertainment/hindi/priya-prakash-varrier-s-viral-wink-sidelined-my-lead-role/videoshow/68101365.cms|title=Priya Prakash Varrier's viral wink sidelined my lead role, claims 'Oru Adaar Love' actress Noorin Shereef|work=The Times of India}}</ref>\n\n==Music==\nThe film music and score were composed by [[Shaan Rahman]].<ref name=\"Shaan\">{{cite news |author=Manoj Kumar R |date=13 February 2018 |title=I wanted Vineeth Sreenivasan's voice to be the highlight of Manikya Malaraya Poovi: Oru Adaar Love composer Shaan |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/malayalam/oru-adaar-love-composer-global-hit-jmalayalam-song-priya-prakash-varrier-5060924/ |editor=G.S VASU |work=[[The New Indian Express]] |location=India |access-date=13 February 2018}}</ref> The song \"Manikya Malaraya Poovi\" sung by [[Vineeth Sreenivasan]], a revised modern version of a [[Mappila Songs|Mappila song]], was uploaded on 9 February 2018 on [[YouTube]] as part of the promotions. It became a [[viral video]] at number 1 position garnering over one million views and 50,000 likes in 20 hours.<ref name=\"manorama\">{{cite news|title=This song from 'Oru Adaar Love' is a hit, social media go bonkers, the heroine of this movie Priya Prakash Varrier is a sensational trend on Twitter and Youtube|url=http://english.manoramaonline.com/entertainment/music/2018/02/11/this-song-from-oru-adaar-love-is-a-hit-social-media-go-bonkers.html|accessdate=12 February 2018|publisher=[[Malayala Manorama]]|date=11 February 2018}}</ref> The original version of \"Manikya Malaraya Poovi\" was written by P. M. A. Jabbar with music composition by Thalassery K. Refeeque in 1978.<ref name=\"Original Song\">{{cite news |author=Express Web desk|date=14 February 2018 |title=Here is the story behind Manikya Malaraya Poovi and the man who wrote it |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/malayalam/manikya-malaraya-poovi-oru-adaar-love-real-story-5064253/ |editor=G.S VASU |work=[[The New Indian Express]] |location=India |access-date=14 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Oru Adaar Love\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Shaan Rahman]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 2019\n| recorded   = 2018\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Soundtrack]]\n| length     = 28:05\n| label      = [[Muzik 247]]\n| producer   = [[Shaan Rahman]]\n| prev_title = [[9 (2019 film)|9]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title = [[Sachin (film)|Sachin]]\n| next_year  = 2019\n| misc       = {{External media\n | audio1     = {{YouTube|oVhr7fekTY8|Official Audio Jukebox}}\n}}}}\n{{tracklist\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| total_length = 24:07\n| title1 = Manikya Malaraya Poovi\n| extra1 = [[Vineeth Sreenivasan]]\n| lyrics1 = [https://ml.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E0%B4%AA%E0%B4%BF.%E2%80%8B%E0%B4%8E%E0%B4%82.%E2%80%8B%E0%B4%8E._%E0%B4%9C%E0%B4%AC%E0%B5%8D%E0%B4%AC%E0%B4%BE%E0%B5%BC P. M. A. Jabbar]\n| length1 = 3:20\n| title2 = Freak Penne\n| extra2 = Sathyajith, Neethu Naduvathettu\n| lyrics2 = [[Sathyajith]]\n| length2 = 3:21\n| title3 = Munnale Ponaale\n| extra3 = [[Haricharan]]\n| lyrics3 = [[Pearle Maaney]]\n| length3 = 3:52\n| title4 = Thanananana Penne\n| extra4 = [[Sooraj Santhosh]], Sruthy Sivadas\n| lyrics4 = B. K. Harinarayanan\n| length4 = 2:47\n| title5 = Forever Friend\n| extra5 = [[Sachin Warrier]]\n| lyrics5 = Sathyajith\n| length5 = 3:27\n| title6 = Aarum Kaanaathinnen\n| extra6 = Vineeth Sreenivasan\n| lyrics6 = B. K. Harinarayanan\n| length6 = 3:00\n| title7 = Maahiya\n| extra7 = [[Hesham Abdul Wahab]], Jeenu Nazeer\n| lyrics7 = B. K. Harinarayanan\n| length7 = 4:20\n| all_writing = \n| title8 = Manichettan Song\n| length8 = \n| title9 = \n| length9 = \n| title10 = \n| length10 = \n}}\n\n==Release==\n''Oru Adaar Love'' was released on 14 February 2019.<ref>{{cite news|last=Hooli|first=Shekhar H.|title=Oru Adaar Love (OAL) movie review and rating by audience: Live updates|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/oru-adaar-love-osl-movie-review-rating-by-audience-live-updates-791897|accessdate=14 February 2019|work=[[International Business Times]]|date=14 February 2019}}</ref> It was dubbed in [[Tamil language|Tamil]] with the same title, in [[Kannada]] as ''Kirik Love Story'' and in [[Telugu language|Telugu]] as ''Lover's Day''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Oru Adaar Love: A perfect film for Valentine's Day|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/oru-adaar-love-movie-review-a-perfect-film-for-valentines-day-oru-adaar-love-review/articleshow/67979619.cms|accessdate=14 February 2019|work=[[The Times of India]]}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n\n=== Box office ===\nAs of 9 March 2019, the film has grossed more than {{INR}}12 crore in India. It was made on a budget of {{INR}}5 crore.<ref name=\"gross\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/omar-lulu-lashes-out-priya-prakash-varrier-says-he-not-touch-actress-793486|title=Omar Lulu lashes out at Priya Prakash Varrier, says he is not in touch with actress|first=Nirmal|last=Narayanan|date=9 March 2019|website=International Business Times, India Edition}}</ref>\n\n=== Critical reception ===\nS.R. Praveen of ''[[The Hindu]]'' stated \"Oru Adaar Love on a Valentine\u2019s day seems to be the handiwork of the culture police, for love hardly ever got such a shabby treatment on screen. If only a wink could save this experiment in mediocrity\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/oru-adaar-love-review-an-experiment-in-mediocrity/article26283386.ece|title=\u2018Oru Adaar Love\u2019 review: An experiment in mediocrity|website=The Hindu|date=2019-02-14|access-date=2019-12-06}}</ref>\n''[[The Times of India]]'' gave 2.5 out of 5 stars stating \"Oru Adaar Love seems like a quickly put together movie trying to cash in on the rather unexpected publicity that came its way. There are unpredictable twists in the tale, however, that may keep viewers hooked till the end\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movie-reviews/oru-adaar-love/movie-review/67991076.cms|title=ORU ADAAR LOVE MOVIE REVIEW|website=Times of India|date=2019-02-14|access-date=2019-12-06}}{{Rating|2.5|5}}</ref>\n''[[India Today]]'' gave 2 out of 5 stars stating \"Oru Adaar Love's lacklustre story and underdeveloped character arcs struggle hard to entertain the audience throughout the film\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/reviews/story/oru-adaar-love-movie-review-roshan-abdul-steals-the-show-in-priya-prakash-varrier-film-1456091-2019-02-14|title=Oru Adaar Love Movie Review: Roshan Abdul and Noorin are stars in Priya Prakash Varrier film|website=India Today|date=2019-02-14|access-date=2019-12-06}}{{Rating|2|5}}</ref>\n\n''[[The News Minute]]'' gave 1 out of 5 stars stating \"The film appears to say that the wrongs that men do aren\u2019t really all that wrong. The misogyny doesn\u2019t even try to hide behind any \u2018larger\u2019 story like in some movies\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/oru-adaar-love-review-priya-prakash-varier-s-wink-can-t-save-disaster-96721|title=\u2018Oru Adaar Love\u2019 review: Priya Prakash Varier\u2019s wink can\u2019t save this disaster|website=The News Minute|date=2019-02-14|access-date=2019-12-06}}{{Rating|1|5}}</ref>\n''[[Times Now]]'' gave 2 out of 5 stars stating \"The film does no justice to the title but you can watch it to reminisce about your high school days and your first crushes. But when it comes to high school romances, I would still prefer watching Trisha Krishnan-Vijay Sethupathi\u2019s 96\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/reviews/movies/article/oru-adaar-love-movie-review-not-priya-prakash-varrier-but-roshan-abdul-rahoof-is-the-star-of-omar-lulus-film/365760|title=Oru Adaar Love movie review: Not Priya Prakash Varrier but Roshan Abdul Rahoof is the star of Omar Lulu's film|website=Times Now|date=2019-02-14|access-date=2019-12-06}}{{Rating|2|5}}</ref>\n''[[The Week (Indian magazine)|The Week]]'' gave 1 out of 5 stars stating \"One of the oft used cliches when reviewing a movie is 'old wine in new bottle'. In Omar Lulu's case, he has just a bottle and filled with some water that has the colour of wine\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.theweek.in/review/movies/2019/02/14/Oru-Adaar-Love-review-No-you-would-not-want-to-take-this-ride.html|title=Oru Adaar Love review: No, you would not want to take this ride|website=The Week|date=2019-02-14|access-date=2019-12-06}}{{Rating|1|5}}</ref>\n\n''[[CNN-News18]]'' gave 2 out of 5 stars stating \"Everything has been planned conveniently to suit a violent ending. What could have turned into an engaging tale of teenage realisation ends up nowhere. It\u2019s a lost opportunity\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/oru-adaae-love-movie-review-priya-prakash-varriers-viral-wink-goes-in-vain-2036387.html|title=Oru Adaar Love Movie Review: Priya Prakash Varrier\u2019s Viral Wink Goes In Vain|website=News18|date=2019-02-14|access-date=2019-12-06}}{{Rating|2|5}}</ref>\n''[[The Indian Express]]'' gave 2 out of 5 stars stating \"Oru Adaar Love has no plot as such except for a predictable romantic triangle that plays out between Priya Prakash Varrier, Roshan Abdul Rahoof and Noorin Shereef. The point the film tries to make hasn\u2019t been fleshed out fully to last a two-hour long narration. The entire movie feels like one big set up to achieve a moment that\u2019s fashioned to make the audience sob\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/oru-adaar-love-movie-review-priya-prakash-varrier-rating-5584130/|title=Oru Adaar Love movie review: Where\u2019s the plot?|website=The Indian Express|date=2019-02-14|access-date=2019-12-06}}{{Rating|2|5}}</ref>\n''Sify'' gave 2 out of 5 stars stating \"Oru Adaar Love provides some unexpected surprises but you would require real patience to sit through until then. It\u2019s a no brainer, often offensive school kid romance that uses every technique to entertain. If that is your idea of fun, you may find this one fine\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.sify.com/movies/oru-adaar-love-review-low-brow-entertainer-review-malayalam-tcovvehjbhfec.html|title=Oru Adaar Love review: Low brow entertainer|website=Sify|date=2019-02-14|access-date=2019-12-06}}{{Rating|2|5}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|7387300}}\n\n[[Category:2010s Malayalam-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:Films about Indian weddings]]\n[[Category:Indian teen films]]\n[[Category:Films set in schools]]\n[[Category:Malayalam-language films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2018 film by Omar Lulu}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Oru Adaar Love\n| image          = Oru Adaar Love (2018) Poster.jpg\n| alt            = The poster features Priya Prakash Varrier and Roshan Abdul Rahoof\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Omar Lulu]]\n| producer       = Ousepachan Vaalakuzhy\n| screenplay     = {{plainlist|\n* Sarang Jayaprakash\n* Lijo Panadan\n}}\n| story          = Omar Lulu\n| starring       = {{plainlist|\n*[[mohammad roshan]]\n*[[Noorin Shereef]]\n*[[Priya Prakash Varrier]]\n}}\n| narrator       = \n| music          = [[Shaan Rahman]]<br/> [[Gopi Sunder]]\n| cinematography = Sinu Sidharth\n| editing        = Achu Vijayan\n| studio         = Ousepachan Movie House\n| distributor    = Ousepachan Screen Media\n| released       = {{Film date|df=y|2019|2|14}}\n| runtime        = 145 minutes <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt7387300/|title=Oru Adaar Love|via=www.imdb.com}}</ref>\n| country        = India\n| language       = [[Malayalam]]\n| budget         = {{INR}}5 crore<ref name=\"gross\" />\n| gross          = {{INR}}12 crore<ref name=\"gross\" />\n}}\n'''''Oru Adaar Love''''' ({{translation |A fantastic love}}) is a 2019 Indian [[Malayalam]]-language [[romantic comedy]] film directed by [[Omar Lulu]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Soman|first1=Deepa|title=Omar Lulu's next film is 'Oru Adaar Love'|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/omar-lulus-next-film-is-oru-adaar-love/articleshow/60531587.cms|accessdate=12 February 2018|work=The Times of India|date= January 2018}}</ref> The screenplay was written by Sarang Jayaprakash and Lijo Panadan from a story by Omar Lulu, and produced by Ousepachan Vaalakuzhy under his production company Ousepachan Movie House.<ref name=\"manorama\"/> The film features [[Roshan Abdul Rahoof]], [[Noorin Shereef]], [[Priya Prakash Varrier]], [[Siyadh Shajahan]], [[Vaishak Pavanan]] and [[Michelle Ann Daniel]] and principal roles.\n\nThe story deals with [[Education in India|high school]] romance. [[Oru Adaar Love]] gained nationwide attention due to a clip which went viral, from the song \"Manikya Malaraya Poovi\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IkTlfPa_E8A|title=Priya Varrier: The actress whose wink stopped India|first=|last=|date=12 March 2018|publisher=BBC News|via=YouTube}}</ref> It prompted the makers to make changes in script, which delayed production.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telugu360.com/oru-adaar-love-reshoot-increase-length-character/|title=\"Oru Adaar Love\" reshoot to increase length of Character|date=9 April 2018|publisher=}}</ref> The film was released on 14 February 2019. It was dubbed and released in [[Tamil language|Tamil]] with the same title as [[Malayalam]] title, in [[Kannada]] as ''[[Kirik Love Story]]''<ref>{{citation|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/priya-prakash-varriers-kannada-dubbed-version-of-oru-adaar-love-to-release-on-valentines-day/articleshow/67349022.cms|title=Priya Prakash Varrier's Kannada dubbed version of 'Oru Adaar love' to release on valentine's day|date=2019-02-01|work=[[The Times of India]]}}</ref> and in [[Telugu language|Telugu]] as ''Lover's Day''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/allu-arjun-be-special-guest-lover-s-day-audio-launch-95459|work=The Newsminute |title=Allu Arjun to be special guest at 'Lover's Day' audio launch|date=22 January 2019|access-date=2019-01-23}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n\nThe story revolves around the journey of high school kids from the time they first meet during their first day of class in 11th class until their graduation day in 12th class. Roshan woos Priya with the help of Gadha and his other friends. One evening Roshan  his friends get drunk and a friend of Roshan accidentally sends a [[porn video]] from Roshan's phone to the school's WhatsApp group. This causes a wedge between Roshan and Priya. Roshan and Gadha then pretend to be in love to make Priya jealous but they end up having feelings for each other. Priya approaches Roshan and says that she is o forgive him and that they can start to be in a relationship again. But Roshan is unable to forget Gadha, which comes to be known by Priya. Heartbroken, she tells Roshan that Gadha alone is the perfect for him and they end their relationship. On graduation day, Roshan decides to propose to Gadha on top of the mountain. Just as Roshan is about to propose to Gadha, they are attacked by a bunch of goons who were antagonized by Roshan and Gadha earlier as part of an [[Eve teasing|eve-teasing]] incident. When Gadha was about to be raped and Roshan to be killed, their friends enter and save them. The movie ends with them riding away happily.\n\n==Cast==\n{{colbegin}}\nPrincipal members of the cast are:<ref>{{cite news|last=Shrijith|first=Sajin|title=Trolling worked to our advantage, says 'Oru Adaar Love' producer Ousepachan Vaalakuzhy|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/2018/dec/17/everything-has-turned-out-well-1912401.html|accessdate=14 February 2019|work=[[The New Indian Express]]|date=17 December 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Roshan Abdul Rahoof]] as Roshan\n* [[Noorin Shereef]] as Gadha John\n* [[Priya Prakash Varrier]] as Priya Varrier\n* [[Siyadh Shajahan]] as Francis E. Manavalan\n* [[Mathew Joseph]] as Mathew\n* [[Arun A Kumar]] as Arun\n* [[Vaishak Pavanan]] as Vishakh aka 'Pavanna'\n* [[Michelle Ann Daniel]] as Michelle\n* [[Aneesh G Menon]] as Shibu Sir, Maths Teacher\n* [[Hareesh Kanaran]] as Unmesh Sir, P. T. Teacher\n* [[Roshna Ann Roy]] as Sneha Miss, Biology Teacher\n* [[Althaf Salim]] as Manikandan Sir, Chemistry Teacher\n* [[Anjali Nair]] as English Miss\n* [[Pradeep Kottayam]] as Principal's Secretary\n* [[Shivaji Guruvayoor]] as Principal\n* [[Siddique (actor)|Siddique]] as Jose Panadan, Sub-Inspector of Police\n* [[Sreejith Ravi]] as Divakaran, Constable of Police\n* [[Salim Kumar]] as Manavalan\n* [[Vishnu Govindan]] as the school peon\n* [[Dilruba Aswad Alqamar]] as Sana\n* [[Suhaid(Kukku)]] as Akku\n* [[Kalabhavan Niyas]] as Gadha's father\n{{colend}}\n\n==Production==\nFilming started on Januay 15, 2018.[http://onlookersmedia.in/latestnews/oru-adaar-love-omar-lulus-next-chunkzz-starts-rolling/ Oru Adaar Love: Omar Lulu\u2019s next after Chunkzz starts rolling!]\nMalayalam film producer Ousepachan Vaalakuzhy, impressed with Omar Lulu's ''[[Happy Wedding]]'' and ''[[Chunkzz]]'' decided to finance his third project, ''Oru Adaar Love''. The primary cast was selected through audition. Ousepachan Vaalakuzhy said he likes to promote newcomers, as has he done with his previous films.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u0d12\u0d2e\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d \u0d1a\u0d3f\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d46 \u0d1e\u0d3e\u0d28\u0d4d\u200d \u0d15\u0d3e\u0d23\u0d41\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d24\u0d4d \u0d12\u0d30\u0d41 \u0d2a\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d38\u0d4d\u0d31\u0d4d\u0d31\u0d40\u0d1c\u0d4d\u0d2f\u0d38\u0d4d \u0d38\u0d3f\u0d28\u0d3f\u0d2e\u0d2f\u0d3e\u0d2f\u0d3f- \u0d28\u0d3f\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d\u0d2e\u0d4d\u0d2e\u0d3e\u0d24\u0d3e\u0d35\u0d4d \u0d14\u0d38\u0d47\u0d2a\u0d4d\u0d2a\u0d1a\u0d4d\u0d1a\u0d28\u0d4d\u200d \u0d05\u0d2d\u0d3f\u0d2e\u0d41\u0d16\u0d02|url=https://southlive.in/movie/interview-movie/ousepachan-interview/|accessdate=12 February 2018|publisher=South Live|date=14 January 2018}}</ref> After Priya Prakash Varrier's wink in the song \"Manikya Malaraya Poovi\" became a viral hit, the makers altered the script to give prominence to her, thus sidelining the role played by Noorin Shereef, who had initially been cast in the lead role.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/videos/entertainment/hindi/priya-prakash-varrier-s-viral-wink-sidelined-my-lead-role/videoshow/68101365.cms|title=Priya Prakash Varrier's viral wink sidelined my lead role, claims 'Oru Adaar Love' actress Noorin Shereef|work=The Times of India}}</ref>\n\n==Music==\nThe film music and score were composed by [[Shaan Rahman]].<ref name=\"Shaan\">{{cite news |author=Manoj Kumar R |date=13 February 2018 |title=I wanted Vineeth Sreenivasan's voice to be the highlight of Manikya Malaraya Poovi: Oru Adaar Love composer Shaan |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/malayalam/oru-adaar-love-composer-global-hit-jmalayalam-song-priya-prakash-varrier-5060924/ |editor=G.S VASU |work=[[The New Indian Express]] |location=India |access-date=13 February 2018}}</ref> The song \"Manikya Malaraya Poovi\" sung by [[Vineeth Sreenivasan]], a revised modern version of a [[Mappila Songs|Mappila song]], was uploaded on 9 February 2018 on [[YouTube]] as part of the promotions. It became a [[viral video]] at number 1 position garnering over one million views and 50,000 likes in 20 hours.<ref name=\"manorama\">{{cite news|title=This song from 'Oru Adaar Love' is a hit, social media go bonkers, the heroine of this movie Priya Prakash Varrier is a sensational trend on Twitter and Youtube|url=http://english.manoramaonline.com/entertainment/music/2018/02/11/this-song-from-oru-adaar-love-is-a-hit-social-media-go-bonkers.html|accessdate=12 February 2018|publisher=[[Malayala Manorama]]|date=11 February 2018}}</ref> The original version of \"Manikya Malaraya Poovi\" was written by P. M. A. Jabbar with music composition by Thalassery K. Refeeque in 1978.<ref name=\"Original Song\">{{cite news |author=Express Web desk|date=14 February 2018 |title=Here is the story behind Manikya Malaraya Poovi and the man who wrote it |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/malayalam/manikya-malaraya-poovi-oru-adaar-love-real-story-5064253/ |editor=G.S VASU |work=[[The New Indian Express]] |location=India |access-date=14 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Oru Adaar Love\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Shaan Rahman]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 2019\n| recorded   = 2018\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Soundtrack]]\n| length     = 28:05\n| label      = [[Muzik 247]]\n| producer   = [[Shaan Rahman]]\n| prev_title = [[9 (2019 film)|9]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title = [[Sachin (film)|Sachin]]\n| next_year  = 2019\n| misc       = {{External media\n | audio1     = {{YouTube|oVhr7fekTY8|Official Audio Jukebox}}\n}}}}\n{{tracklist\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| total_length = 24:07\n| title1 = Manikya Malaraya Poovi\n| extra1 = [[Vineeth Sreenivasan]]\n| lyrics1 = [https://ml.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E0%B4%AA%E0%B4%BF.%E2%80%8B%E0%B4%8E%E0%B4%82.%E2%80%8B%E0%B4%8E._%E0%B4%9C%E0%B4%AC%E0%B5%8D%E0%B4%AC%E0%B4%BE%E0%B5%BC P. M. A. Jabbar]\n| length1 = 3:20\n| title2 = Freak Penne\n| extra2 = Sathyajith, Neethu Naduvathettu\n| lyrics2 = [[Sathyajith]]\n| length2 = 3:21\n| title3 = Munnale Ponaale\n| extra3 = [[Haricharan]]\n| lyrics3 = [[Pearle Maaney]]\n| length3 = 3:52\n| title4 = Thanananana Penne\n| extra4 = [[Sooraj Santhosh]], Sruthy Sivadas\n| lyrics4 = B. K. Harinarayanan\n| length4 = 2:47\n| title5 = Forever Friend\n| extra5 = [[Sachin Warrier]]\n| lyrics5 = Sathyajith\n| length5 = 3:27\n| title6 = Aarum Kaanaathinnen\n| extra6 = Vineeth Sreenivasan\n| lyrics6 = B. K. Harinarayanan\n| length6 = 3:00\n| title7 = Maahiya\n| extra7 = [[Hesham Abdul Wahab]], Jeenu Nazeer\n| lyrics7 = B. K. Harinarayanan\n| length7 = 4:20\n| all_writing = \n| title8 = Manichettan Song\n| length8 = \n| title9 = \n| length9 = \n| title10 = \n| length10 = \n}}\n\n==Release==\n''Oru Adaar Love'' was released on 14 February 2019.<ref>{{cite news|last=Hooli|first=Shekhar H.|title=Oru Adaar Love (OAL) movie review and rating by audience: Live updates|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/oru-adaar-love-osl-movie-review-rating-by-audience-live-updates-791897|accessdate=14 February 2019|work=[[International Business Times]]|date=14 February 2019}}</ref> It was dubbed in [[Tamil language|Tamil]] with the same title, in [[Kannada]] as ''Kirik Love Story'' and in [[Telugu language|Telugu]] as ''Lover's Day''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Oru Adaar Love: A perfect film for Valentine's Day|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/oru-adaar-love-movie-review-a-perfect-film-for-valentines-day-oru-adaar-love-review/articleshow/67979619.cms|accessdate=14 February 2019|work=[[The Times of India]]}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n\n=== Box office ===\nAs of 9 March 2019, the film has grossed more than {{INR}}12 crore in India. It was made on a budget of {{INR}}5 crore.<ref name=\"gross\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/omar-lulu-lashes-out-priya-prakash-varrier-says-he-not-touch-actress-793486|title=Omar Lulu lashes out at Priya Prakash Varrier, says he is not in touch with actress|first=Nirmal|last=Narayanan|date=9 March 2019|website=International Business Times, India Edition}}</ref>\n\n=== Critical reception ===\nS.R. Praveen of ''[[The Hindu]]'' stated \"Oru Adaar Love on a Valentine\u2019s day seems to be the handiwork of the culture police, for love hardly ever got such a shabby treatment on screen. If only a wink could save this experiment in mediocrity\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/oru-adaar-love-review-an-experiment-in-mediocrity/article26283386.ece|title=\u2018Oru Adaar Love\u2019 review: An experiment in mediocrity|website=The Hindu|date=2019-02-14|access-date=2019-12-06}}</ref>\n''[[The Times of India]]'' gave 2.5 out of 5 stars stating \"Oru Adaar Love seems like a quickly put together movie trying to cash in on the rather unexpected publicity that came its way. There are unpredictable twists in the tale, however, that may keep viewers hooked till the end\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movie-reviews/oru-adaar-love/movie-review/67991076.cms|title=ORU ADAAR LOVE MOVIE REVIEW|website=Times of India|date=2019-02-14|access-date=2019-12-06}}{{Rating|2.5|5}}</ref>\n''[[India Today]]'' gave 2 out of 5 stars stating \"Oru Adaar Love's lacklustre story and underdeveloped character arcs struggle hard to entertain the audience throughout the film\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/reviews/story/oru-adaar-love-movie-review-roshan-abdul-steals-the-show-in-priya-prakash-varrier-film-1456091-2019-02-14|title=Oru Adaar Love Movie Review: Roshan Abdul and Noorin are stars in Priya Prakash Varrier film|website=India Today|date=2019-02-14|access-date=2019-12-06}}{{Rating|2|5}}</ref>\n\n''[[The News Minute]]'' gave 1 out of 5 stars stating \"The film appears to say that the wrongs that men do aren\u2019t really all that wrong. The misogyny doesn\u2019t even try to hide behind any \u2018larger\u2019 story like in some movies\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/oru-adaar-love-review-priya-prakash-varier-s-wink-can-t-save-disaster-96721|title=\u2018Oru Adaar Love\u2019 review: Priya Prakash Varier\u2019s wink can\u2019t save this disaster|website=The News Minute|date=2019-02-14|access-date=2019-12-06}}{{Rating|1|5}}</ref>\n''[[Times Now]]'' gave 2 out of 5 stars stating \"The film does no justice to the title but you can watch it to reminisce about your high school days and your first crushes. But when it comes to high school romances, I would still prefer watching Trisha Krishnan-Vijay Sethupathi\u2019s 96\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/reviews/movies/article/oru-adaar-love-movie-review-not-priya-prakash-varrier-but-roshan-abdul-rahoof-is-the-star-of-omar-lulus-film/365760|title=Oru Adaar Love movie review: Not Priya Prakash Varrier but Roshan Abdul Rahoof is the star of Omar Lulu's film|website=Times Now|date=2019-02-14|access-date=2019-12-06}}{{Rating|2|5}}</ref>\n''[[The Week (Indian magazine)|The Week]]'' gave 1 out of 5 stars stating \"One of the oft used cliches when reviewing a movie is 'old wine in new bottle'. In Omar Lulu's case, he has just a bottle and filled with some water that has the colour of wine\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.theweek.in/review/movies/2019/02/14/Oru-Adaar-Love-review-No-you-would-not-want-to-take-this-ride.html|title=Oru Adaar Love review: No, you would not want to take this ride|website=The Week|date=2019-02-14|access-date=2019-12-06}}{{Rating|1|5}}</ref>\n\n''[[CNN-News18]]'' gave 2 out of 5 stars stating \"Everything has been planned conveniently to suit a violent ending. What could have turned into an engaging tale of teenage realisation ends up nowhere. It\u2019s a lost opportunity\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/oru-adaae-love-movie-review-priya-prakash-varriers-viral-wink-goes-in-vain-2036387.html|title=Oru Adaar Love Movie Review: Priya Prakash Varrier\u2019s Viral Wink Goes In Vain|website=News18|date=2019-02-14|access-date=2019-12-06}}{{Rating|2|5}}</ref>\n''[[The Indian Express]]'' gave 2 out of 5 stars stating \"Oru Adaar Love has no plot as such except for a predictable romantic triangle that plays out between Priya Prakash Varrier, Roshan Abdul Rahoof and Noorin Shereef. The point the film tries to make hasn\u2019t been fleshed out fully to last a two-hour long narration. The entire movie feels like one big set up to achieve a moment that\u2019s fashioned to make the audience sob\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/oru-adaar-love-movie-review-priya-prakash-varrier-rating-5584130/|title=Oru Adaar Love movie review: Where\u2019s the plot?|website=The Indian Express|date=2019-02-14|access-date=2019-12-06}}{{Rating|2|5}}</ref>\n''Sify'' gave 2 out of 5 stars stating \"Oru Adaar Love provides some unexpected surprises but you would require real patience to sit through until then. It\u2019s a no brainer, often offensive school kid romance that uses every technique to entertain. If that is your idea of fun, you may find this one fine\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.sify.com/movies/oru-adaar-love-review-low-brow-entertainer-review-malayalam-tcovvehjbhfec.html|title=Oru Adaar Love review: Low brow entertainer|website=Sify|date=2019-02-14|access-date=2019-12-06}}{{Rating|2|5}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|7387300}}\n\n[[Category:2010s Malayalam-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:Films about Indian weddings]]\n[[Category:Indian teen films]]\n[[Category:Films set in schools]]\n[[Category:Malayalam-language films]]\n", "name_user": "Bri", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePlot:un-pipe proper name", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oru_Adaar_Love"}
